    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="115"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/417.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>German Government agrees to postponement of the opium conference to February 1
                    next.</p>
                <p>Herr Roessler, consul at Canton and first German commissioner, has been given
                    rank and character of consul general for the period of the conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
